benin – Assistant Inspector of General Police (AIG) in charge of Zone 5, comprising Edo, Delta and Bayelsa States, Baba Alkali Usman, on Thursday while assuring the electorate in the zone of police preparedness for a peaceful election in 2019, directed Commissioners of Police (CPs) in the three states to urgently convey a security summit. The summit, he explained for all political parties and their candidates will be held to discuss the conduct of the 2019 elections. Usman, however assured that the police and other security agencies including the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC), will provide a level playing ground to all political parties and their candidates during the 2019 elections. Baba Usman, who addressed journalists in Benin on Thursday shortly after a marathon meeting with the Commissioners of Police from Edo, Delta, Bayelsa, INEC officials from the zone and Heads of Operations and officers in charge of Political desks, promised that the police and other security agencies will work assiduously to ensure a hitch free election in the zone. He said, “There is need for INEC to collaborate and synergize with the police and other security agencies to ensure a hitch free political campaigns in the 2019 elections. “The CPs from Edo, Delta and Bayelsa States commands should put up robust strategies and supervise the conduct of political parties and their candidates during the political campaigns. “They should as a matter of urgency reactivate the Agency for Consultative Forum chaired by the Commissioner and co-chaired by INEC REC in their respective commands, on how they will discuss and conduct a hitch free 2019 election.” He appealed to the political parties and their supporters to cooperate with the police and other security agencies by seeking permission or notifying them on their political rallies to avoid clashes with other parties before or after the rallies. AIG Usman advised INEC to ensure proper training of ad hoc staff and police personnel who would take part in the elections.